(RewardLoopWorker pid=955548, ip=10.124.44.153) The Royal Navy's first fast battleships were the **Hawkins-class** and **King George V-class** battleships. These ships were designed to be faster and more maneuverable than traditional battleships, making them suitable for both World War I and World War II. The Hawkins-class, launched in the 1920s, was the first of these fast battleships, while the King George V-class, launched in the 1930s, became the most numerous and widely used of the fast battleships in the Royal Navy.
